  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-7 clean Not-accepted)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed, 6 factors scoped-out (acceptable at MRL 2). One assessed factor (Discretization error) achieved Gradation 1 against a required Gradation 2, representing a documented shortfall. The decision is Not accepted pending remediation of the mesh-refinement study to achieve Richardson extrapolation convergence at the impeller tip region.",
