        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Numerical code verification acceptance criteria — MRL 2",
        "description": "Gradation 2 requires demonstration that the solver correctly implements governing equations through at least one benchmark problem with known analytical or manufactured solution."
      },
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent passes the FDA critical path benchmark (pipe flow and backward-facing step) with errors below 2% against analytical solutions. Method of manufactured solutions results are documented in the solver qualification package. Gradation 2 achieved."
