      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-disc-error-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria — MRL 2",
        "description": "Gradation 2 requires a systematic mesh refinement study with at least three mesh levels and a documented Grid Convergence Index (GCI) or Richardson extrapolation estimate for the primary QoI (relative hemolysis index) demonstrating convergence within 5% of the extrapolated value."
      },
      "rationale": "Only two mesh levels were evaluated (4.2 M and 8.7 M cells). Richardson extrapolation requires a minimum of three systematically refined meshes to compute a reliable observed order of accuracy. The impeller tip gap region exhibits non-monotonic convergence between the two available levels, indicating the asymptotic range has not been reached. GCI cannot be reliably estimated. This shortfall constitutes a Gradation 1 achievement against the Gradation 2 requirement and is the primary basis for the Not-accepted decision."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-test-conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
