      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-test-conditions-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria — MRL 2",
        "description": "Gradation 2 requires that bench test boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity and density) are documented and traceable to calibrated measurement equipment with stated uncertainties."
      },
      "rationale": "Five operating points (2.5 and 5.0 L/min at 2500, 3500, and 4500 RPM) were tested in the Morrison et al. flow loop. Inlet flow measured with a Coriolis meter (±0.5% FS), RPM verified with a tachometer (±5 RPM). Fluid: bovine blood analogue at 37 °C, viscosity 3.5 ± 0.1 mPa·s. All boundary conditions documented and traceable. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
