        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison acceptance criteria — MRL 2",
        "description": "Gradation 2 requires quantitative comparison of model predictions against experimental measurements for at least the primary QoI, with documented agreement metrics (e.g., NRMSE, E_avg) and stated experimental uncertainty bounds."
      },
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) predicted by CFD compared against bench measurements at all five operating points. Mean absolute error 8.3%, within experimental uncertainty bands (±12%). Velocity field compared against PIV data with NRMSE 6.1% across the mid-plane. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-relevance-qoi",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-relevance-qoi-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Relevance of QoI acceptance criteria — MRL 2",
        "description": "Gradation 2 requires documented justification that the chosen QoI (relative hemolysis index) is directly linked to the clinical endpoint and that the hemolysis power-law model parameters are appropriate for the flow regime."
      },
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index (RH = NIH_device / NIH_predicate) is the FDA-accepted metric for comparative hemolysis assessment. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model with parameters calibrated for shear-dominated flow is appropriate for the impeller tip region where peak shear stress exceeds 150 Pa. Justification documented in the V&V plan. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
